message.content:
1. Patients received 8 mg VM202 per leg.
2. These patients showed improvement in all efficacy measures.
3. There was a significant reduction in the mean pain score at 3 months.
4. The significance level of the reduction in pain score at 3 months was P = 0.03.
5. There were continued reductions in pain at 6 and 9 months.
6. The reductions in pain at 6 and 9 months were not statistically significant.

messages.content:
Statement: Patients receiving 8 mg VM202 per leg improved the most in all efficacy measures including a significant (P = 0.03) reduction at 3 months in the mean pain score and continued but not statistically significant reductions in pain at 6 and 9 months.
